Vusi Nhlakanipho Zuma died on Sunday night at the Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg following a short illness Details surrounding the death of Jacob Zuma’s son, Vusi, will be conveyed by midday, Zuma’s spokesperson Vukile Mathabele said. “The family will appoint a spokesperson before midday,” he told African News Agency. Vusi was one of five children born to Jacob Zuma and Kate Manthso, including twins Duduzane and Duduzile Zuma. Manthso committed suicide in 2000. – African News Agency 